Opportunity for Youth

The Wilkinson Center recently received a youth grant through Workforce Solutions. The program is part of the WIOA, and they are recruiting out of school youth, ages 17-24. They offer high school equivalency classes, job search assistance, connection to post-secondary or vocational training, financial coaching and case management. Participants in the program, if eligible, will receive transportation assistance, vouchers to pay for their GED tests and other supportive services such as work uniforms. Contact Rachel Berhe at rachael_berhe@wilkinsoncenter.org for more information.

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT
text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

THE TEXAS NATIONAL GUARD JOINS THE NORTH TEXAS FOOD BANK FOR DISASTER RELIEF MOBILE PANTRY STOP AT FAIR PARK

The North Texas Food Bank (NTFB), in conjunction with the Texas National Guard, Fair Park First, Spectra, and In the City for Good, is returning to Fair Park to distribute free food on Thursday, April 16 from 9:00 AM until 12:00 PM, or until all available food has been distributed.

Thursday, April 16 from 9:00 AM ‚Äì 12:00 PM, or until all available food has been distributed. Food pantry guest‚Äôs vehicles will not be allowed to enter the Fair Park grounds until 8:15 AM or later.

The pick-up location will be in Lots 5A and 6A, located in between Robert B Cullum Boulevard and 2nd Avenue inside Fair Park. Participants should enter through Gate 5 only, located at the intersection of Robert B Cullum Boulevard and Grand Avenue. The Dallas Police Department will be onsite to assist with traffic flow.

Please bring your ID!

Visit www.ntfb.org/mobile-pantry for information on other NTFB Disaster Relief Mobile Pantry events.

post_text:
On November 23, parents, students, and teachers spent the day serving and giving back! Volunteers participated in various ways to serve, such as creating an English & Spanish Cafeteria Word Wall, removing trash and debris from the playground, repairing the west side deck of the PreK building, and planting a tree in honor of a BP student. With the help of our volunteers, 24 Thanksgiving Baskets were also assembled and donated to the Wilkinson Center. What a great way to kick off the start of the Thanksgiving holiday!

#MyBP #MyCityscape #FamilyVolunteerDay #GivingBack #DallasCharterSchools

BP will celebrate UNITY DAY on October 23rd. All students are encouraged to wear and share ORANGE to show that we are together against bullying and UNITED for kindness, acceptance, and inclusion!

Students may:
1. Choose something orange they already have, such as clothing, jewelry, or accessories. They can wear a T-shirt of their choice, shoelaces, socks, bandanna, or sunglasses.
2. Create their own orange, like wearing an orange bracelet made from ribbon or construction paper.
